In any distribution of assets on liquidation of a savings and loan association, the priority of claims is as follows:
In a mutual association:
General creditors and holders of savings deposit accounts;
Holders of savings share accounts; and
Contributors to the initial general reserve fund before June 1, 1986 and to the expense fund under Subtitle 2 of this title; and
In a capital stock association:
General creditors (other than those who are capital stockholders) and holders of savings deposit accounts;
Holders of savings share accounts;
Contributors to the initial general reserve fund before June 1, 1986 and to the expense fund under Subtitle 2 of this title unless the funds were provided by paid-in surplus; and
Capital stockholders.
